comments:
That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of Stoke Climsland. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

Created 1.4.1922 from the parishes of St. Mary Magdalene, St. 
    Stephens by Launceston Urban, St. Thomas Street, St. Thomas the Apostle Urban and Lawhitton Urban. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Lawhitton Urban 
    and Lawhitton Rural.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Lawhitton. See 
    also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Lawhitton in Launceston 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish of Launceston 
    (otherwise Dunheved).

Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish of Launceston 
    (otherwise Dunheved).

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of St. Stephens 
    in Launceston Urban and St. Stephens in Launceston Rural.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of St. Stephens. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of St. Stephens in Launceston 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish of Launceston 
    (otherwise Dunheved).

Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish of Launceston 
    (otherwise Dunheved).

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of St. Thomas the 
    Apostle Urban and St. Thomas the Apostle Rural.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of St. Thomas the 
    Apostle. See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of St. Thomas the Apostle 
    in Launceston Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1922 and added to the parish 
    of Launceston (otherwise Dunheved).
